<item>
            <title>[LU-19414] &quot;lctl get_param --dshbak&quot; does not print actual parameter name. </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19414</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &quot;lctl get_param --dahbak&quot; command will highlight if parameters report different results. However, it doesn&apos;t print the actual parameter name that is different, only &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#42;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; for the merged parameter names:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&#160; &#160; lustre-head# lctl set_param osc.myth-OST0004-osc-ffff9a4dc70f5800.max_pages_per_rpc=256
&#160; &#160; osc.myth-OST0004-osc-ffff9a4dc70f5800.max_pages_per_rpc=256
&#160; &#160; lustre-head# lctl get_param -b osc.*.max_pages_per_rpc
&#160; &#160; osc.myth-OST*-osc-ffff9a4dc70f5800.max_pages_per_rpc=1024
&#160; &#160; osc.myth-OST*-osc-ffff9a4dc70f5800.max_pages_per_rpc=256
&#160;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;it should have printed the second line with the actual &quot;OST0004&quot; in the device name  instead of &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#42;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to make it clear which device is not like the others.  Ideally, it would print the minority device(s) in red, rather than the second one, but I don&apos;t know how hard that is to implement. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
